{
  "doc_id": "99",
  "text": "The existent uncertain programming methods such as stochastic programming (see, e.g., [CITATION_1] ), fuzzy programming (see, e.g., [CITATION_2] ) and interval programming (see, e.g., [CITATION_3] ) can not solve the PUNP problem directly. It is noted that there are many contributions which deal with the simple polymorphic uncertain linear program (PULP). For example, in [CITATION_4] , the multi-objective linear programming problem containing fuzzy random parameters is solved by fuzzy random simulation. In [CITATION_5] , a class of mix design linear programming problems involved with interval and random coefficients is studied to find an optimal mixture scheme. In [CITATION_6] , a hybrid two-stage stochastic optimization model is constructed for the regional energy systems planning which is associated with interval, fuzzy and random parameters.",
